## Flashing Oculus Firmware

Depending on when you got your Oculus HMD you might need to update your firmware.
The current firmware version is listed in the Oculus Configuration Utility. 
If your firmware version is not using the latest version, complete the following steps to update the HMD firmware.

1. Click on **Tools > Advanced > Update Firmware**.

	![](Platforms\Oculus\QuickStart\4\UpdateFirmware_menu.png)

	[REGION:note]
	Make sure Unreal Editor, Unreal Engine Launcher, and any other programs that might be using the Oculus are closed before you update the firmware. Otherwise, you will get a warning about closing other software and the firmware will not install.
	[/REGION]

1. Select the firmware when the file dialog appears, then click **Open**. In this image we are using version 2.12.

	![](Platforms\Oculus\QuickStart\4\Firmware.png)

1. The **Oculus Configuration Utility** will close. Reopen it by:

	* Opening the Start Menu and navigating to **Oculus Runtime > OculusConfigUtil**, or
	* Running `OculusConfigUtil.exe` found in `[InstallDirectory]/Tools/`.

1. Verify that the firmware is the one you installed by going to **Help** and clicking on **About**. From this menu you will be able to determine which version of the Oculus drivers you are using.

	![](Oculus_Current_Firmware.png)

